The paper focuses on distributed graph algorithms, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of algebraic techniques and fast matrix multiplication suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Computational Complexity (cs.CC). The specific graph problems studied, such as triangle detection and all-pairs shortest path, suggest that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Graph Theory (cs.GT) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
